;; Upstream python-stdnum modules we intentionally do NOT mirror as public types.
;; Subtracted from the New-modules bucket so they never show as parity gaps.
;;
;; - Checksum algorithms are implemented inline in stdnum.core, not exposed as
;;   dispatchable types (we expose :luhn only).
;; - :ean is python's generic EAN module; we expose the finer :ean8 / :ean13 instead.
;; - :gs1_128 is a GS1-128 barcode Application-Identifier parser (AI database, FNC1
;;   element strings returning a parsed map), not a single-number validator; it sits
;;   outside stdnum-clj's valid?/parse/format model, and upstream is still changing its
;;   AI handling (PR #498). Deliberately not mirrored.
;;
;; Only add a module here once you've made a deliberate decision not to expose it.
;; A genuinely-missing type belongs in the report, not here.
#{:damm
  :verhoeff
  :ean
  :gs1_128
  :iso7064-mod_11_10
  :iso7064-mod_11_2
  :iso7064-mod_37_2
  :iso7064-mod_37_36
  :iso7064-mod_97_10}
